      "widgets_values": [
        "\n📌 ComfyUI Workflow Notes\n\nAuthor: Sharvin Suntoobacus\n\nYouTube Channel: CodeCraftersCorner\n\nPatreon: Support on Patreon\n\n---\n\nℹ️ About This Workflow\n\nThis workflow provides a streamlined implementation of Meta’s Segment Anything Model 3.1 (SAM 3.1) using native ComfyUI nodes. Users will be able to perform high-precision image masking and automated multi-object video tracking via text prompts or visual cues without requiring third-party custom nodes.\n\n---\n\n🎥 Tutorial / Guide\n[Watch on YouTube](https://youtu.be/oMJVkMUqx30)\n\n📥 Model Links (for Local Users)\n**Checkpoints**\n- [sam3.1_multiplex_fp16.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/sam3.1/tree/main)\n    \n\n📂 Model Storage Location\nPlace the downloaded files into the following directories within your ComfyUI installation. **Note:** SAM 3.1 is currently utilized via the checkpoints directory in this native setup.\n\n```\n📂 ComfyUI/\n├── 📂 models/\n│ ├── 📂 checkpoints/\n│ │ └── sam3.1_multiplex_fp16.safetensors\n```\n\n💡 Notes\n\n- **Multiple Objects:** Use the syntax `label:number` (e.g., `person:2`) to detect multiple instances of the same class.\n    \n- **Video Trimming:** For optimal performance, trim videos to the specific segments where the subject is present to reduce processing time.\n    \n- **Refinement:** If masks are inaccurate or jagged, increase the **Refine Iterations** or adjust the **Threshold** settings within the SAM3 Detect node.\n    \n- **Requirements:** Ensure your ComfyUI and ComfyUI Manager are updated to the latest versions to access native SAM 3.1 support.\n    \n\nCredit: Please credit Sharvin Suntoobacus and share YouTube Channel Code Crafters Corner when sharing this workflow.\n\nSupport: Your support on Patreon helps me continue creating these guides!\n\n[YouTube Channel](https://www.youtube.com/@codecrafterscorner) | [Patreon Page](https://www.patreon.com/codecrafterscorner)\n\n🙏 Thank you for your support!"
